00:00:07,759 --> 00:00:09,850
we're going to do in this segment,

4
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:11,590
we need our income statement.

5
00:00:11,590 --> 00:00:15,270
So the first column and the third column

6
00:00:15,270 --> 00:00:20,940
shows Amazon's and Walmart's income statements in 2016.

7
00:00:20,940 --> 00:00:25,950
Again, Amazon is a much smaller company than Walmart.

8
00:00:25,950 --> 00:00:29,340
So, to compare the companies apples to apples,

9
00:00:29,340 --> 00:00:31,710
we're going to common size them.

10
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:35,460
And a typical way to common size an income statement is

11
00:00:35,460 --> 00:00:37,830
divide all the numbers by sales, which

12
00:00:37,830 --> 00:00:43,260
is what's being done in columns 2 and columns 4.

13
00:00:43,260 --> 00:00:46,530
So you can see, once this comparison is made,

14
00:00:46,530 --> 00:00:51,840
that Walmart has a bigger cost of sales than does Amazon.

15
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:55,410
Amazon, on the other hand, has more selling, general,

16
00:00:55,410 --> 00:00:58,590
and administrative expense than does Walmart.

17
00:00:58,590 --> 00:01:02,320
Now, this probably makes sense because Amazon

18
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:03,950
is an online retailer.

19
00:01:03,950 --> 00:01:08,470
So their cost of sales are lower, but, remember,

20
00:01:08,470 --> 00:01:10,930
Amazon has this additional cost, which

21
00:01:10,930 --> 00:01:13,585
is the shipping cost, which is probably

22
00:01:13,585 --> 00:01:15,730
what's showing up in the bigger selling, general,

23
00:01:15,730 --> 00:01:18,560
and administrative number.

24
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:20,210
And then we go down.

25
00:01:20,210 --> 00:01:25,280
We see that net income for Walmart is 3% of sales,

26
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:29,540
whereas net income for Amazon is only 2% of sales.

27
00:01:29,540 --> 00:01:31,430
So neither one of these companies

28
00:01:31,430 --> 00:01:34,730
has a big what we call profit margin,

29
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:40,260
but Walmart has a slightly higher profit than does Amazon.

30
00:01:40,260 --> 00:01:45,800
So profitability ratios, the one side of profitability ratios

31
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,520
are margins.

32
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,300
So the basic profitability ratio is what's

33
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,520
called net margin percentage.

34
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,280
It's often just called profit margin.

35
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:59,760
And it's net income divided by revenues.

36
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,890
And then you can go up the income statement

37
00:02:01,890 --> 00:02:03,480
and form other margins.

38
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:06,510
So you can go up a little bit and form the operating margin

39
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:10,229
percentage, which is operating profits to revenues.

40
00:02:10,229 --> 00:02:12,570
And then you can go up even higher

41
00:02:12,570 --> 00:02:15,870
and form the gross margin percentage, which

42
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:17,400
is gross profits to revenues.

43
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:20,140


44
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:23,055
