00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:48,410
is 1.74%, whereas Walmart's, again, is 3.04%.

51
00:02:48,410 --> 00:02:50,790
Another set of profitability ratios--

52
00:02:50,790 --> 00:02:53,090
so the profitability ratios we just did

53
00:02:53,090 --> 00:02:58,710
were take an income number and divide it by sales.

54
00:02:58,710 --> 00:03:01,220
The other thing that investors care about a lot

55
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:05,180
is how much income management is generating

56
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:07,550
per unit of investment, so income

57
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:11,660
as a percent of investment or return on investment.

58
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:15,080
And there are lots and lots of different flavors of this,

59
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:18,710
but I want to introduce you to two flavors, which

60
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:23,660
is return on assets, which is some income number divided

61
00:03:23,660 --> 00:03:26,900
by total assets--

62
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:29,830
and there's a variety of income numbers used.

63
00:03:29,830 --> 00:03:31,900
We're going to focus on net income

64
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:35,500
for reasons that will become clear in a few minutes.

65
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:39,240
But other ones are earnings without interest expense

66
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,780
divided by total assets.

67
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:43,560
So that's a return on assets number.

68
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:48,360
Or we might use EBITDA, which is Earnings Before Interest, Tax,

69
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:52,140
and Depreciation, and Amortization,

70
00:03:52,140 --> 00:03:53,850
divided by investment.

71
00:03:53,850 --> 00:03:57,090
And that's a different type of return on assets number.

72
00:03:57,090 --> 00:03:59,820
So, when we test you, it'll always be clear

73
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:01,620
what number we're using.

74
00:04:01,620 --> 00:04:05,940
In the real world, people talk about return on assets.

75
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:07,800
And the number that they are thinking

76
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,890
about in the numerator of that calculation

77
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:12,760
often can vary a bit.

78
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:15,870
So you just want to be clear about the context

79
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:19,290
when you're talking to somebody.

80
00:04:19,290 --> 00:04:21,850
So that's return to all investors,

81
00:04:21,850 --> 00:04:24,810
which is return on assets.

82
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:28,690
Stockholders' in particular care about their returns.

83
00:04:28,690 --> 00:04:31,660
So their investment is stockholders' equity.

84
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:35,160
And so we've already defined return on equity

85
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:40,480
as net income divided by stockholders' equity.

86
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:44,100
And here it's a question of which stockholders' equity

87
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:46,660
number do we use.

88
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:49,270
So, for this course and in this class,

89
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:52,545
we're going to focus on ending stockholders' equity.

90
00:04:52,545 --> 00:04:55,950
So you can get that right off of the balance sheet.

91
00:04:55,950 --> 00:04:57,360
It's easier to get.

92
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:00,210
There's more data available.

93
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:03,260
Conceptually, average stockholders' equity

94
00:05:03,260 --> 00:05:06,080
is the better number, but that involves

95
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:09,650
collecting this year's balance sheet, last year's balance

96
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:13,580
sheet, averaging the two stockholders' equity numbers.

97
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:17,240
So there's more calculation involved.

98
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:21,080
It's better theoretically because the income

99
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:24,500
that we generate this period is mainly

100
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:28,460
being generated by beginning stockholders' equity.

101
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:31,160
As we add net income to that, we're

102
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:35,570
generating income off of that new stockholders' equity

103
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:36,290
number.

104
00:05:36,290 --> 00:05:39,830
And that's why average stockholders' equity is

105
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:42,520
at least theoretically better.

